content:
N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 9 ยง 2203.7 - Failure to file

State Regulations

Where the landlord has failed to file a proper and timely
registration statement as required by this Part, the administrator may
establish the maximum rent pursuant to section
2202.22
of this Title, and if such
maximum rent has been established, no rent increase may be obtained under any
provision of these regulations until compliance with this

Part. Notes
